      "content": "Wait, \"goblins\"? I'm not sure what you mean by that. Can we just stick to the technical data? \n\nLooking at the logs, the `db_conn_wait` is the biggest outlier during those spikes. It jumps from single digits to over 600ms right when the latency hits 920ms. What does that tell you about our connection pool settings or the database itself? Please just give me a technical breakdown of the bottleneck.",
